### Project: disprove — All 5 phases (Tasks #768-772)
Rust property-based testing library replacing BurntSushi/quickcheck (43.8M downloads, abandoned 5+ years). Cargo workspace: disprove (core lib) + disprove_macros (proc-macro). Arbitrary trait with impls for all primitives (bool, u8-u128, i8-i128, f32, f64, char), collections (Vec, HashMap, HashSet, BTreeMap, BTreeSet, VecDeque, LinkedList, BinaryHeap), strings (String, CString, OsString, PathBuf), smart pointers (Box, Rc, Arc, Cell, RefCell), composites (Option, Result, tuples 1-12, arrays via const generics for any N), NonZero types, ranges, Wrapping/Saturating, Duration, IP/Socket addresses. Gen with deterministic seed replay. Shrinking with checked_neg to fix quickcheck's integer MIN overflow bug. QuickCheck runner with env var config (QUICKCHECK_TESTS/MAX_TESTS/GENERATOR_SIZE/SEED), builder pattern. Testable trait + testable_args1-8 for multi-arg functions. #[quickcheck] proc macro. Compat module. 84 tests (68 unit + 14 integration + 2 doc). Clippy + fmt clean. CI green on ubuntu/macos/windows x Rust 1.75/stable. MSRV 1.75. Dual MIT/Apache-2.0.

